The White House Domestic Policy Council held a listening session with over sixty presidents and chancellors of Historically Black Colleges and Universities (HBCUs). Before the session, the HBCU leaders met with President Trump and Secretary of Education Betsy DeVos. Vice President Mike Pence and Secretary DeVos addressed the HBCU leaders during the session, which also included representatives from various government departments and White House offices. The leaders discussed ways to improve education and infrastructure at their schools, and shared insights on policy issues. Vice President Pence emphasized President Trump's commitment to prioritizing HBCUs, and participants discussed creating a better partnership between the Trump Administration and HBCUs. Representatives from leading HBCU organizations also attended the session.